    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix missing command type handling in CMEE response encoding\n\n### Summary\nThe AT command response encoder for CMEE (mobile termination error reporting) was not explicitly handling all AT command types, causing unexpected behavior when called with SET or ACT commands. While the function technically worked correctly by returning 0 bytes for unhandled command types, it wasn't clear that this was the intended behavior.\n\nThe issue manifested when users tried to set CMEE mode (AT+CMEE=<n>) and expected either a response or clear indication that no response is generated. The lack of explicit handling made the code difficult to maintain and understand.\n\nThis bug was introduced when the CMEE response encoder was originally implemented without considering all possible AT command types that might be passed to it.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/UE/API/USER/at_response.c`: Added explicit comment indicating that AT_COMMAND_SET and AT_COMMAND_ACT do not generate response text for CMEE, making the behavior clear for future maintainers.\n\n"
}